{"config":{"lang":["pt","en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"2026.1-compiladores","text":"Luan Mateus William Soares"},{"location":"grammar/","title":"Gram\u00e1tica","text":"<p>Gram\u00e1tica da linguagem.</p>"},{"location":"grammar/#program","title":"program:","text":"<pre><code>program  ::= stmts\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"grammar/#stmts","title":"stmts:","text":"<pre><code>stmts    ::= stmt*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>for_stmt</li> <li>program</li> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#stmt","title":"stmt:","text":"<pre><code>stmt     ::= 'if' '(' expr ')' '{' stmts '}' ( 'else' 'if' '(' expr ')' '{' stmts '}' )* ( 'else' '{' stmts '}' )?\n           | for_stmt\n           | puts_stmt\n           | var_stmt\n           | const_stmt\n           | assign_stmt\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>stmts</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#var_stmt","title":"var_stmt:","text":"<pre><code>var_stmt ::= 'var' IDENTIFIER type ':=' expr ';'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>for_stmt</li> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#const_stmt","title":"const_stmt:","text":"<pre><code>const_stmt\n         ::= 'const' IDENTIFIER type ':=' expr ';'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#assign_stmt","title":"assign_stmt:","text":"<pre><code>assign_stmt\n         ::= IDENTIFIER ':=' expr ';'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#assign_expr","title":"assign_expr:","text":"<pre><code>assign_expr\n         ::= IDENTIFIER ':=' expr\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>for_stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#for_stmt","title":"for_stmt:","text":"<pre><code>for_stmt ::= 'for' '(' ( var_stmt | ';' ) expr ';' assign_expr? ')' '{' stmts '}'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#puts_stmt","title":"puts_stmt:","text":"<pre><code>puts_stmt\n         ::= 'puts' '(' expr ')' ';'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#type","title":"type:","text":"<pre><code>type     ::= 'int'\n           | 'flt'\n           | 'chr'\n           | 'str'\n           | 'boo'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>const_stmt</li> <li>var_stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#expr","title":"expr:","text":"<pre><code>expr     ::= logical_or\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>assign_expr</li> <li>assign_stmt</li> <li>const_stmt</li> <li>for_stmt</li> <li>primary</li> <li>puts_stmt</li> <li>stmt</li> <li>var_stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#logical_or","title":"logical_or:","text":"<pre><code>logical_or\n         ::= logical_and ( '||' logical_and )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>expr</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#logical_and","title":"logical_and:","text":"<pre><code>logical_and\n         ::= equality ( '&amp;&amp;' equality )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>logical_or</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#equality","title":"equality:","text":"<pre><code>equality ::= comparison ( ( '!=' | '==' ) comparison )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>logical_and</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#comparison","title":"comparison:","text":"<pre><code>comparison\n         ::= addition ( ( '&gt;' | '&gt;=' | '&lt;' | '&lt;=' ) addition )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>equality</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#addition","title":"addition:","text":"<pre><code>addition ::= multiplication ( ( '+' | '-' ) multiplication )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>comparison</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#multiplication","title":"multiplication:","text":"<pre><code>multiplication\n         ::= modulo ( ( '*' | '/' ) modulo )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>addition</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#modulo","title":"modulo:","text":"<pre><code>modulo   ::= unary ( '%' unary )*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>multiplication</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#unary","title":"unary:","text":"<pre><code>unary    ::= ( '!' | '+' | '-' )* primary\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>modulo</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#primary","title":"primary:","text":"<pre><code>primary  ::= INT\n           | FLT\n           | CHR\n           | STR\n           | BOO\n           | IDENTIFIER\n           | '(' expr ')'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>unary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#identifier","title":"IDENTIFIER:","text":"<pre><code>IDENTIFIER\n         ::= [a-zA-Z_] [a-zA-Z0-9_]*\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>assign_expr</li> <li>assign_stmt</li> <li>const_stmt</li> <li>primary</li> <li>var_stmt</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#int","title":"INT:","text":"<pre><code>INT      ::= [0-9]+\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>primary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#flt","title":"FLT:","text":"<pre><code>FLT      ::= [0-9]+ '.' [0-9]+\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>primary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#chr","title":"CHR:","text":"<pre><code>CHR      ::= \"'\" [^'] \"'\"\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>primary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#str","title":"STR:","text":"<pre><code>STR      ::= '\"' [^\"]* '\"'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>primary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#boo","title":"BOO:","text":"<pre><code>BOO      ::= 'true'\n           | 'false'\n</code></pre> <p>referenced by:</p> <ul> <li>primary</li> </ul>"},{"location":"grammar/#_1","title":"Gram\u00e1tica","text":"<p> <sup>generated by RR - Railroad Diagram Generator</sup></p>"},{"location":"syntax/","title":"Sintaxe","text":"<p>Sintaxe da linguagem.</p>"},{"location":"syntax/#palavras-reservadas","title":"Palavras Reservadas","text":"<pre><code>const\nvar\nint\nflt\nchr\nboo\nstr\ntrue\nfalse\nfuck\nret\nputs\nfor\nif\nelse\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#comentarios","title":"Comentarios","text":"<p>A linguagem <code>fucklang</code> s\u00f3 tem suporte a coment\u00e1rio de linha, feito com o <code>#</code>.</p> <pre><code># comment\u00e1rio\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#constantes","title":"Constantes","text":"<pre><code>const a int := 1;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#variaveis","title":"Vari\u00e1veis","text":"<pre><code>var x int := 10;\nvar y flt := 3.14;\nvar z chr := 'a';\nvar s str := \"hello\";\nvar b boo := true;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#operadores","title":"Operadores","text":""},{"location":"syntax/#aritmeticos","title":"Aritm\u00e9ticos","text":"<p>Precisam ser do mesmo tipo.</p> <pre><code>x + y   # adi\u00e7\u00e3o\nx - y   # subtra\u00e7\u00e3o\nx * y   # multiplica\u00e7\u00e3o\nx / y   # divis\u00e3o\nx % y   # resto\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#comparacao","title":"Compara\u00e7\u00e3o","text":"<pre><code>x &gt; y   # maior que\nx &lt; y   # menor que\nx &gt;= y  # maior ou igual\nx &lt;= y  # menor ou igual\nx == y  # igual\nx != y  # n\u00e3o igual (diferente)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#logicos","title":"L\u00f3gicos","text":"<pre><code>x &amp;&amp; y  # E\nx || y  # OU\n!x      # N\u00e3o/Nega\u00e7\u00e3o\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#condicionais","title":"Condicionais","text":""},{"location":"syntax/#if","title":"if","text":"<pre><code>if (1 &lt; 10) {\n    puts(1);\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#if-else-if","title":"if-else-if","text":"<pre><code>if (10 &lt; 10) {\n    puts(1);\n} else if (10 == 10) {\n    puts(10);\n} else {\n    puts(100);\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#if-else","title":"if-else","text":"<pre><code>if (100 &lt; 10) {\n    puts(10);\n} else {\n    puts(100);\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#loops","title":"Loops","text":"<p>A linguagem <code>fucklang</code> s\u00f3 tem suporte ao <code>for</code>, seja criativo com ele para simular o <code>while</code>.</p> <pre><code>for (var i int := 0; i &lt; 10; i := i + 1) {\n    puts(i);\n}\n</code></pre> <p><code>for</code> como <code>while</code>: <pre><code>var i int := 0;\nfor (;i &lt; 10;) {\n    puts(i);\n    i := i + 1;\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"syntax/#funcoes","title":"Fun\u00e7\u00f5es","text":"<p>fuck</p> <p>N\u00e3o implementado.</p> <pre><code>fuck print_x() {\n    puts('x');\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"syntax/#exemplo","title":"Exemplo","text":"<pre><code># even numbers\nvar number_two int := 2;\nvar number_limit int := 10;\n\nfor (var i int := 0; i &lt;= number_limit; i := i + 1) {\n    if (i % number_two == 0) {\n        # print even number\n        puts(i);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/grammar/","title":"Grammar","text":"<p>Grammar of the language.</p>"},{"location":"en/grammar/#_1","title":"Grammar","text":"<p> <sup>generated by RR - Railroad Diagram Generator</sup></p>"},{"location":"en/syntax/","title":"Syntax","text":"<p>Language syntax.</p>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#reserved-words","title":"Reserved Words","text":"<pre><code>const\nvar\nint\nflt\nchr\nboo\nstr\ntrue\nfalse\nfuck\nret\nputs\nfor\nif\nelse\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#comments","title":"Comments","text":"<p>The <code>fucklang</code> language only supports single-line comments, using <code>#</code>.</p> <pre><code># comment\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#constants","title":"Constants","text":"<pre><code>const a int := 1;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#variables","title":"Variables","text":"<pre><code>var x int := 10;\nvar y flt := 3.14;\nvar z chr := 'a';\nvar s str := \"hello\";\nvar b boo := true;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#operators","title":"Operators","text":""},{"location":"en/syntax/#arithmetic","title":"Arithmetic","text":"<p>Operands must be of the same type.</p> <pre><code>x + y   # addition\nx - y   # subtraction\nx * y   # multiplication\nx / y   # division\nx % y   # remainder\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#comparison","title":"Comparison","text":"<pre><code>x &gt; y   # greater than\nx &lt; y   # less than\nx &gt;= y  # greater than or equal to\nx &lt;= y  # less than or equal to\nx == y  # equal to\nx != y  # not equal to\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#logical","title":"Logical","text":"<pre><code>x &amp;&amp; y  # AND\nx || y  # OR\n!x      # NOT/Negation\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#conditionals","title":"Conditionals","text":""},{"location":"en/syntax/#loops","title":"Loops","text":"<p>The <code>fucklang</code> language only supports <code>for</code> loops; be creative with them to simulate <code>while</code> loops.  <pre><code>for (var i int := 0; i &lt; 10; i := i + 1) { \n    puts(i);\n}\n</code></pre></p> <p><code>for</code> as <code>while</code>: <pre><code>var i int := 0;\nfor (;i &lt; 10;) { \n    puts(i); \n    i := i + 1;\n}\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#functions","title":"Functions","text":"<p>fuck</p> <p>Not implemented.</p> <pre><code>fuck print_x() { \n    puts('x');\n}\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/syntax/#example","title":"Example","text":"<pre><code># even numbers\nvar number_two int := 2;\nvar number_limit int := 10;\n\nfor (var i int := 0; i &lt;= number_limit; i := i + 1) { \n    if (i % number_two == 0) { \n        # print even number \n        puts(i); \n    }\n}\n</code></pre>"}]}